edu.cornell.georeference

Class GeoDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cornell.georeference.GeoDataSource

  • public class GeoDataSource
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the data source. It stores all information needed to build the index from the data source.
    Author:
    Yang Yang Zheng

      • GeoDataSource

        public GeoDataSource(java.lang.String filePath,
             java.lang.String datSourceSplitString,
             int numOfCols,
             int nameColNum,
             int altName1ColNum,
             int altName2ColNum,
             int latColNum,
             int lngColNum,
             boolean ignoreFirstRow)
        Create the data source using the file path and other details.
        Parameters:
        filePath - the path to the data source file
        datSourceSplitString - what string is used to separate different fields in the data file
        numOfCols - number of columns in the data file
        nameColNum - the column number for the name column
        altName1ColNum - the column number of the first alternative name column
        altName2ColNum - the column number of the second alternative name column
        latColNum - the column number of the latitude column
        lngColNum - the column number of the longitude column
        ignoreFirstRow - whether or not to ignore the first row when reading in the file (some files have the column names as the first row)

      • GeoDataSource

        public GeoDataSource(java.lang.String filePath,
             java.lang.String datSourceSplitString,
             int numOfCols,
             java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> colNumMap,
             boolean ignoreFirstRow)
        Create the data source using the file path and other details.
        Parameters:
        filePath - the path to the data source file
        datSourceSplitString - what string is used to separate different fields in the data file
        numOfCols - number of columns in the data file
        colNumMap - a map that maps field name to the column number (must use the field names in the GeoIndexWriter class)
        ignoreFirstRow - whether or not to ignore the first row when reading in the file (some files have the column names as the first row)

        public static GeoDataSource createGeoNamesDataSource(java.lang.String filePath)
        Creates a GeoDataSource object from the data that come from this website: http://www.geonames.org/
        Parameters:
        filePath - the path to the data file
        Returns:
        the GeoDataSource object that represent the data source and can be used by GeoIndexWriter to create index/directory

        Returns:
